Shopping Habits:
Ethan's shopping habits are primarily focused on acquiring art supplies and materials to support his creative endeavors. He scours secondhand stores, online platforms, and discount art supply retailers to find affordable, high-quality materials that he can use in his work. He is mindful of his spending and often prioritizes necessities over discretionary purchases.

Professional Life:
As a self-employed artist, Ethan's professional life is a constant balancing act between creating his art and finding ways to generate income. He spends long hours in his studio, experimenting with various mediums and techniques to develop his unique artistic style. He actively seeks out opportunities to showcase his work, whether through local art exhibitions, online galleries, or commission-based projects.

Personal Style:
Ethan's personal style reflects his creative and introspective nature. He favors a casual, yet thoughtful, approach to fashion, often donning well-worn jeans, comfortable t-shirts, and a variety of layering pieces that allow him to adapt to the changing weather and demands of his artistic work. His attire is functional and practical, allowing him to move freely and focus on his craft.

